<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="431" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,656,683]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
As for genus; endophallus in ventral view with conspicuous arcuate component transverse in relation to median elongate tubular structure and a slightly asymmetrical group of several sclerites directed distad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="433" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,728,755]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Description.</emphasis>
Body of male (
<figureCitation box="[524,654,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Dorsal (20–21) and ventral (22) habitus. Abbreviations: bef, basal elytral foveae; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; psp, prosternal process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602454/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Figs 20–21</figureCitation>
) elongate, strongly convex, dark reddish-brown, setae yellowish; BL 
<quantity box="[151,254,765,791]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" unit="mm" value="1.14">1.14 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,476,1079]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[274,403,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Dorsal (20–21) and ventral (22) habitus. Abbreviations: bef, basal elytral foveae; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; psp, prosternal process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602454/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Figs 20–21</figureCitation>
) broadest at moderately large, strongly convex eyes, HL 
<quantity box="[1048,1149,801,827]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<quantity box="[1215,1319,801,827]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" unit="mm" value="0.28">0.28 mm</quantity>
; frons and vertex confluent and weakly convex. Punctures on vertex and frons distinct, large and deep, densely and unevenly distributed, those on median area distinctly sparser, separated by spaces 1.5–2 × as wide as diameters of punctures, on sides of frons and vertex punctures separated by spaces subequal to their diameters; setae short, sparse and recumbent. Antennae (
<figureCitation box="[386,469,945,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,662,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[159,1428,661,1781]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Head in dorsal (23) and ventral (24–25) views; right antenna in dorsal view (26); right protarsus and apex of tibia in dorsal view (27); prothorax in ventral (28) and lateral (29) view; pterothorax in ventral view (30). Abbreviations: bst, basisternum; fg, frontal gland; fr, frons; gp, gular plate; gs, gular suture; hyr, hypomeral ridge; ic, internal cavity; lbr, labrum; lp, labial palp; lpc, lateral pronotal carina; md, mandible; mn, mentum; mscc, mesocoxal cavity; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; mxp1–4, maxillary palpomere I–IV; nss, notosternal suture; pcc, procoxal cavity; pcr, procoxal rest; pmn, prementum; psp, prosternal process; smn, submentum; vl, velum; vt, vertex; lfa, lateral furcal arm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602458/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) slender, AnL 
<quantity box="[638,742,945,971]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" unit="mm" value="0.43">0.43 mm</quantity>
; antennomere I only slightly elongate, II about twice as long as broad; III–VII each about as long as broad or barely noticeably broader than long, VIII distinctly transverse, IX slightly transverse, distinctly longer but only slightly broader than VIII, X about as long as broad, much larger than IX, XI about 1.8 × as long as broad, as broad as X and slightly longer than IX–X together.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602454" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3602454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602454/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" startId="8.[151,264,1944,1969]" targetBox="[151,1436,1134,1873]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1944,2005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,342,1944,1969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">FIGURES 20–22.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jałoszyński" authorityYear="2020" box="[349,530,1945,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Indomicrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chera">
<emphasis box="[349,530,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Indomicrus chera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[538,677,1944,1969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">gen. &amp; sp. n.</emphasis>
Dorsal (20–21) and ventral (22) habitus. Abbreviations: bef, basal elytral foveae; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; psp, prosternal process.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,152,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[327,459,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1944,1969]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1134,1873]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–22. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Dorsal (20–21) and ventral (22) habitus. Abbreviations: bef, basal elytral foveae; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; psp, prosternal process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602454" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602454/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">Figs 20–21</figureCitation>
) broadest near middle; PL 
<quantity box="[776,881,153,179]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="9" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
, PW 
<quantity box="[946,1052,152,179]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
. Anterior margin weakly convex, anterior corners subtriangular and blunt, weakly obtuse-angled, lateral margins rounded and shallowly microserrate (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,662,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[159,1428,661,1781]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Head in dorsal (23) and ventral (24–25) views; right antenna in dorsal view (26); right protarsus and apex of tibia in dorsal view (27); prothorax in ventral (28) and lateral (29) view; pterothorax in ventral view (30). Abbreviations: bst, basisternum; fg, frontal gland; fr, frons; gp, gular plate; gs, gular suture; hyr, hypomeral ridge; ic, internal cavity; lbr, labrum; lp, labial palp; lpc, lateral pronotal carina; md, mandible; mn, mentum; mscc, mesocoxal cavity; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; mxp1–4, maxillary palpomere I–IV; nss, notosternal suture; pcc, procoxal cavity; pcr, procoxal rest; pmn, prementum; psp, prosternal process; smn, submentum; vl, velum; vt, vertex; lfa, lateral furcal arm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602458/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
), base arcuate. Pronotal disc slightly flattened near each hind corner, lacking any peculiar structures. Punctures on pronotal disc similar to those on frons and vertex, almost evenly distributed, shallow but sharply marked, separated by spaces 1.5–2 × as wide as diameters of punctures. Basic setae slightly longer than those on frons and vertex, similarly sparse, nearly recumbent, additionally pronotum with four pairs of strikingly long and erect macrosetae: one pair near each hind corner, two lateral pairs near middle of pronotum, and one lateral pair near anterior pronotal margin, behind each eye.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,152,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">
Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[282,381,441,467]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1843,1868]" captionTargetBox="[166,1436,913,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,913,1823]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Foveomicrus indicus gen. &amp; sp. n. Dorsal (1–2) and ventral (3) habitus. Abbreviations: bef, basal elytral foveae; hc, humeral carina; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; pcr, procoxal rest; pf, pronotal foveae; psp, prosternal process." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602448/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">Figs 1–2</figureCitation>
) together oval, broadest distinctly in front of middle; EL 
<quantity box="[1025,1127,440,467]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.65">0.65 mm</quantity>
, EW 
<quantity box="[1188,1290,440,467]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="432" unit="mm" value="0.55">0.55 mm</quantity>
, EI 1.18; hu- meral calli indistinct, humeral denticles well-defined but blunt. Punctures on elytra distinctly larger and sparser than those on pronotum; basic setae similar to those on pronotum, additionally each elytron with over 20 conspicuously long and erect macrosetae distributed all over the surface. Hind wings absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,152,647]" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">
Legs moderately long and slender; protibiae (
<figureCitation box="[721,804,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1801,1826]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,662,1775]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[159,1428,661,1781]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 23–30. Indomicrus chera gen. &amp; sp. n. Head in dorsal (23) and ventral (24–25) views; right antenna in dorsal view (26); right protarsus and apex of tibia in dorsal view (27); prothorax in ventral (28) and lateral (29) view; pterothorax in ventral view (30). Abbreviations: bst, basisternum; fg, frontal gland; fr, frons; gp, gular plate; gs, gular suture; hyr, hypomeral ridge; ic, internal cavity; lbr, labrum; lp, labial palp; lpc, lateral pronotal carina; md, mandible; mn, mentum; mscc, mesocoxal cavity; msvp, mesoventral process; mtvp, metaventral process; mxp1–4, maxillary palpomere I–IV; nss, notosternal suture; pcc, procoxal cavity; pcr, procoxal rest; pmn, prementum; psp, prosternal process; smn, submentum; vl, velum; vt, vertex; lfa, lateral furcal arm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602458/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly thickened distad, each with apical row of six flattened digitiform projections.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3602458" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3602458" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3602458/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="432" startId="9.[151,264,1801,1826]" targetBox="[159,1428,662,1775]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1801,2042]" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,340,1801,1826]" pageId="9" pageNumber="432">FIGURES 23–30.</emphasis>
