<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="433" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="10" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,477,503]" pageId="10" pageNumber="433">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jałoszyński" authorityYear="2020" box="[462,526,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Indomicrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="433" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chera">
<emphasis box="[462,526,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="433">chera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(noun in apposition) refers to the Chera dynasty ruling from the second century BCE in the area of Tamilakam (the ancient Tamil country) that includes the present-day 
<collectingRegion box="[1138,1216,513,539]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="10" pageNumber="433">Kerala</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
